  "texts": [
    "To achieve this, it is imperative to ensure transparency in AI's subgoal-setting algorithms and mechanisms (Hacker et al. 2023).",
    "Establishing safety verification guidelines based on transparency, defining human intervention procedures, and creating continuous regulatory and supervision systems are necessary.",
    "Given the potential risks that may arise from the automated subgoalsetting process of AI, such regulatory approaches are of utmost importance.",
    "The necessity of safety regulatory policies AI regulation in context (with specific IAEA focus).",
    "The rapid advancement of Artificial Intelligence (AI) technology necessitates robust regulatory frameworks to ensure safety and ethical standards."
  ]
